ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A great critical review of experimental methods and their applications that culminates with students conducting their own social science experiment.I would recommend this class to anyone who is, or might be, interested in doing field experiments in their research and hasn't had practical experience with them yet.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I intend to employ field experiments in my research and possibly my dissertation, so this course was very applicable to my progress as a doctoral student and scholar. In addition, this course deepened my understanding of the quantitative methods I studied in other courses since we critiqued applications of those methods.
